<h1 class="hero-h">Fractional CMO New York / NYC <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Remote-first fractional CMO for NYC B2B.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Treetop works with New York City B2B mid-market companies on a remote-first basis. NYC has unique market characteristics — financial services density, professional services, B2B media — that shape the right marketing approach. Here's the framework.</p>
<div class="tldr"><div class="tldr-l">Short answer</div><p class="tldr-p">Treetop offers remote-first fractional CMO services to NYC B2B mid-market companies. Particularly relevant for financial services, professional services, and B2B media verticals concentrated in New York. \$8K-\$25K/month typical.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">NYC B2B market characteristics</h2><p class="body">New York's B2B economy is concentrated in a few high-value verticals that share characteristics:</p><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Financial services / fintech</strong> — dense buyer base, sophisticated buyers, compliance-aware marketing required.</li><li><strong>Professional services</strong> — consulting firms, law firms, accounting practices, agencies. Trust-driven marketing is the right pattern.</li><li><strong>B2B media + marketing tech</strong> — densest cluster in the country.</li><li><strong>Real estate B2B</strong> — proptech, brokerages, property management.</li><li><strong>Healthcare B2B</strong> — large hospital systems, payors, healthcare IT.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Marketing implications</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Generic AI hype doesn't land in NYC buyer culture — substance wins.</li><li>Trust marketing (case studies, relationships, references) outperforms broad-reach campaigns.</li><li>Compliance-aware messaging is required in finserv and healthcare.</li><li>In-person events and conferences still meaningful here in a way they aren't elsewhere.</li><li>Bylined operator-led content from NYC executives reads as authority.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Treetop's NYC engagement model</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Remote-first with quarterly on-site visits.</li><li>1-2 days per week typical cadence.</li><li>Builder profile — we ship, we don't just present.</li><li>AI-fluent — modern fractional CMO work compounds with AI workflows.</li><li>12-18 month commitments for compounding outcomes.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Best-fit NYC clients</h2><ul class="ul"><li>B2B fintech, financial services, or professional services firms at $3M-$30M ARR/revenue.</li><li>Hybrid or remote-friendly teams (we cannot be in NYC five days a week).</li><li>Operators who want AI-augmented marketing operations, not just AI-themed talk.</li><li>Founder-led marketing that has hit its limit.</li></ul></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">FAQ</h2>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you have an NYC office?</h3><p class="faq-qa">No. Remote-first with on-site visits.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">How often will you be in NYC?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Quarterly typically. More for kickoff.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you work with East Coast hours?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — primary operating hours are Eastern/Central time.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you work with financial services?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — common engagement profile.</p></div>
<div class="faq-q"><h3 class="faq-qh">Do you handle compliance-aware marketing?</h3><p class="faq-qa">Yes — we work with regulated finserv and have built marketing engines that respect FINRA/SEC constraints.</p></div>
</div></section>

